Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A poppy field before sunrise, cold enough to show breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.85,0:00:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The pods were scored the evening before and have wept their gum overnight; now a line of scrapers moves down the rows, lifting the grey beads off each pod with a curved iron before the dew burns away.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.64,0:00:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,At the edge of the field, where the rows meet the earthen bund, lies a girl on her side in the dirt: LEELA, sixteen, a printed kameez gone stiff with dew, one slipper on and one in the furrow beside her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.23,0:00:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,An old woman scrapes the row nearest the body without looking at it, her lips going Ram Ram, Ram Ram, her iron not stopping; a boy works behind her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.88,0:00:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A CBN jeep pulls onto the field road.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.77,0:00:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,INSPECTOR RATAN SINGH PANWAR, fifties, heavy, a sweater under his uniform, gets out slowly with a hand on the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.76,0:01:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Constable DEVA, twenty-four, follows a step behind and stays there.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.28,0:01:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,BHERULAL, the girl's father, comes across the field toward them but stops a few rows short of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.04,0:01:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You've come, sahib. At night... who knows why she went out. It was dark. She must have fallen. That's all. Just make out the papers, I'll sign.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.36,0:01:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He still has not looked at her.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.48,0:01:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Who saw her first?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.79,0:01:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The scrapers. They came before dawn... she was lying here. I let no one touch her. She's just as she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.08,0:01:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan crouches beside the girl, slow, a hand on his knee.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.60,0:01:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Deva photographs from the bund.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.06,0:01:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Bherulal turns away, toward the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.36,0:01:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,She was engaged?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.83,0:01:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The boy's people were coming in two days to fix the wedding date. If word spreads now...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.08,0:01:51.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan stands and looks at the scrapers still working the rows around the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.84,0:01:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You've kept the work going.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.19,0:01:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The gum doesn't wait, sahib. Should I... should I just stand here?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.04,0:02:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan looks at the field a moment, then turns to Deva.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.36,0:02:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Clear the field. No scraping today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.72,0:02:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Deva goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.48,0:02:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Down the field the scrapers stop and stand, holding their irons over the gum.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.31,0:02:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Bherulal comes after Ratan.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.64,0:02:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't stop it, sahib. Don't do this. If the crop doesn't come in... sahib, you know. I have nothing else...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.28,0:02:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan looks at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.76,0:02:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Call two more men from the station. No — call four. And send the body to the district hospital for postmortem. We stay here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.64,0:02:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Postmortem? Sahib, she died from a fall. Don't put her through more... just... let her be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.52,0:02:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He does not look at the father.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.40,0:02:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.76,0:02:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Bherulal keeps at him — sahib, think once more — but Ratan has crouched back down beside the girl, and he stays there, and after a while the pleading stops on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.96,0:03:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,A small room off the women's side, thin light through one barred window.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.33,0:03:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole house smells of the gum, in the walls and in the dead girl's clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.22,0:03:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,A string cot, a steel almirah, Leela's Class 10 guidebooks tied with string for the boards three weeks off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.20,0:03:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In the next room a woman's voice goes up — Oh my darling, oh my child — and the others take it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.56,0:03:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,SUGNA sits on the floor with her daughter's clothes in her lap, her shoulders shaking, a fold of the girl's clothes pressed to her mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.84,0:03:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,RATAN fills the doorway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.67,0:03:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He steps in and goes to the almirah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.41,0:03:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Sugna's head comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.36,0:03:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing... these are my child's things.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.52,0:03:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,An AUNT comes in behind him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.64,0:03:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sahib, step outside. This is the women's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.76,0:03:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan does not stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.21,0:04:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He works the lid off a steel tin, and under a fold of cloth finds a smaller cloth knotted tight: a thin roll of tens and twenties and a fist of one-rupee coins, and a coaching-class handbill from Ratlam, soft at the folds from handling.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.60,0:04:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Sugna has got to her feet and reached him, pulling at his arm, at the clothes in his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.56,0:04:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My darling... my child...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.32,0:04:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan looks at the handbill a moment, then folds the cloth back over the money and puts it in his pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.80,0:04:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The aunt comes and takes Sugna by the arm, and Sugna folds against her and lets herself be held.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.00,0:04:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes, out through the keening.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.20,0:04:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A government room gone yellow at the edges — steel almirahs of files, a ceiling fan turning slow, a framed Gandhi over the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.99,0:04:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,SUPERINTENDENT MISHRA sits behind his desk with Leela's thin file open in front of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.65,0:04:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan stands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.64,0:04:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,DEVA waits by the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.68,0:04:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She fell in the field and died, and it's licensed land. The father's ready to sign. What's so much in this, Ratan?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.88,0:04:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I've sent the body for postmortem.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.92,0:04:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Mishra looks up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.40,0:05:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Who sent it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.87,0:05:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.04,0:05:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Mishra sits back, the tiredness of a man who has settled a hundred of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.88,0:05:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a village girl. There's a death in the house, it's a matter of honour. What will you get from cutting her open? Write the report, close it. I'll sign right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.70,0:05:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The father wouldn't leave the crop, sahib. His child lay in front of him, and he was thinking about the harvest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.80,0:05:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Every father's in a hurry. Ratan. Whose licenses run this belt, who stands behind whom — who knows it better than you? Don't put your hand into someone's house for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.64,0:05:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan does not answer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.52,0:05:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The report comes after the postmortem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.72,0:05:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Mishra holds his eye a moment, then drops it back to the file.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.60,0:05:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine. Your report, your responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.28,0:05:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan turns to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.68,0:05:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Deva follows him out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.60,0:05:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan lowers himself into his chair.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.37,0:05:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Deva hovers, the file still in his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.80,0:06:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sahib... Mishra sahib isn't wrong. She must have slipped and fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.68,0:06:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever seen anyone slip and die in a poppy field?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.99,0:06:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,...No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.50,0:06:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither have I.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.24,0:06:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,A beat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.77,0:06:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan does not go on with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.24,0:06:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Order tea, Deva.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.56,0:06:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The field at the end of the day, the lancing stopped on Ratan's order, the gum drying grey and useless on the pods.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.74,0:06:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan walks the bund where the body lay, Deva a step behind with a torch he does not need yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.42,0:06:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,At the field's edge, a well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.41,0:06:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The house two hundred metres off, its one light on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.32,0:06:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The house is there. She was found here, at this end of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.41,0:06:44.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What would she come to this end for, at night?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.88,0:06:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan looks past the well, to a footpath running off into the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.24,0:06:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Where does this path go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.90,0:06:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,To the road. The bus stand's ahead — the Manasa one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.84,0:06:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan stands a while where the path leaves the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.16,0:07:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Who saw her last that night — at home, in the field, on the path. Ask everyone. Write down the names.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.92,0:07:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,An old NIGHT-WATCHMAN sits on a charpai outside a hut, a stick across his knees.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.60,0:07:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Deva has brought him to Ratan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.73,0:07:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He is careful, an old man who has kept his job by not seeing things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.84,0:07:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you on watch that night?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.71,0:07:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was, sahib. My eyes shut for a bit in between.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.92,0:07:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see Leela? Bherulal's girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.88,0:07:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The old man looks at the stick across his knees.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.64,0:07:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,...I saw her. Late at night. Alone, walking fast, toward the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.18,0:07:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Crying? Frightened?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.10,0:07:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so dark, sahib. She was just in a hurry. Whether anyone was behind her, I didn't see. I went back to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.69,0:07:50.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Would anyone else have seen?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.93,0:07:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. Sahib, don't put my name on any paper. I have to live here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.88,0:08:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,A small farming household — a kitchen open to the courtyard, a hand-pump, the smell of frying onion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.48,0:08:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,DEVA's mother, AMMA, works the dough.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.30,0:08:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,His father, BAPU, sits on a charpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.04,0:08:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,SUNITA, eighteen, Deva's sister, moves between them with the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.05,0:08:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,DEVA comes in from the day still in uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.68,0:08:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You're back. Wash up. Listen — Girdhari's son, Vijay. His family's proposing for Sunita.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.55,0:08:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good household. Two bigha of land, a license too. The boy's looking for work in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.56,0:08:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunita sets a bowl down and does not look up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.64,0:08:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Go meet them once. You're in uniform — your word carries weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.90,0:08:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm caught up in a case right now, Amma.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.19,0:08:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Cases will keep coming. The girl's age is slipping by. Well? You say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.34,0:08:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever you think is right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.60,0:09:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Deva looks at his sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.19,0:09:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The day is still on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.00,0:09:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Did anyone ask Sunita?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.80,0:09:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What's there to ask, son? It's a good match. We wouldn't wish her ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.72,0:09:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunita's eyes come up to Deva's for a second — and go back down to the food.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.40,0:09:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So go and meet them. Day after tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.53,0:09:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,...I'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.96,0:09:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunita carries the empty pot to the pump and works the handle, and the water covers whatever she does not say.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.48,0:09:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The house asleep, one low bulb still on in the corner where SUNITA has her bedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.43,0:09:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,She sits up with a school notebook open in her lap and a pen in her hand, not writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.60,0:09:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,From the parents' room, the murmur of the match goes on — Girdhari's boy, two bigha, a license.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.12,0:09:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,She listens to it the way you listen to weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.84,0:09:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Deva comes in for water, sees her awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.92,0:09:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.43,0:10:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you go to meet them? Day after? Them?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.47,0:10:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.76,0:10:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunita closes the notebook and lies down, her face to the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.80,0:10:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave it. Everything's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.80,0:10:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Deva stands with the glass in his hand and does not drink it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.36,0:10:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,A line of licensed growers waits with their season's gum in steel lotas.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.42,0:10:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,At the scale sits KHARE, the measurement officer, fifty and neat, weighing a farmer's lump of latex and writing the figure into a register.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.18,0:10:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A FARMER watches the needle like his life is on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.04,0:10:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's short. Less than last time, even. Mind it next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.76,0:10:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The farmer takes his receipt and goes, not arguing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.30,0:10:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan has come up at the side.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.39,0:10:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Khare sees him, and a practised warmth comes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.00,0:10:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Ratan sahib. I heard about Bherulal's girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.65,0:10:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Does Bherulal give full weight here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.24,0:10:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The pen stops for half a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.44,0:11:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The girl fell and died, sahib. What's Bherulal's license got to do with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.05,0:11:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.76,0:11:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Khare leans in, the practised warmth gone, his voice dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.44,0:11:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan. Bherulal's in debt, and whose debt it is, you know too. Everyone's accounts are running even here. Don't stick your leg in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.35,0:11:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A girl is dead, Khare.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.04,0:11:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Khare goes back to his register and the next man's lota.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.08,0:11:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Girls keep dying around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.96,0:11:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A roadside stall, a kettle, men on a bench with glasses of tea, the bazaar behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.79,0:11:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The talk is the dead girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.96,0:11:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They do not lower their voices much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.24,0:11:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Heard about it? Bherulal's girl. At night, in the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.12,0:11:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What was she doing in the field at night — nobody asks that. Girls these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.27,0:11:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,She was engaged, wasn't she? Into a good family?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.94,0:11:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,She was. God's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.88,0:11:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A third man, older, has been quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.96,0:12:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The CBN man's nosing around. Had a postmortem done.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.09,0:12:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Will he let it go? These people have reach right to the top. Ratan sahib is sensible. He'll get it closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.00,0:12:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They drink their tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.88,0:12:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Tiles, a steel table, a drain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.24,0:12:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Leela's body under a sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.36,0:12:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The medical officer, DOCTOR VERMA, fills a form standing up, wanting to be elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.04,0:12:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan and Deva at the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.44,0:12:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Head injury, from the fall. It's clear. I'm writing 'brought dead'.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.88,0:12:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you send the viscera?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.94,0:12:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What for? The injury's right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.94,0:12:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Lungs, stomach, blood — send all of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.62,0:12:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector, four bodies come here every day. If I sent everyone's viscera the lab would collapse. Has something been said from above?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.55,0:12:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If it had, the word would be to stop it, not to send it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.32,0:12:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Verma looks at him, then at the small shape under the sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.46,0:12:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He folds the sheet back from her face and leans in, and something stops him a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.60,0:13:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The injury is from a fall, but... all right, I'll send it. The report will take a week to ten days.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.49,0:13:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Get it done quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.24,0:13:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Another grower's plot, another lancing crew.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.24,0:13:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The grower, HUKMA, walks Ratan along his rows, easy, the two of them old at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.76,0:13:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the row Hukma folds a few notes into Ratan's hand the way you'd pass a relative something for the children, and Ratan takes them the way you take it, without looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.32,0:13:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If the weighing runs a little off this time... well, you're there, sahib.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.06,0:13:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll see to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.89,0:13:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That Bherulal business... it'll all be set right, won't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.08,0:13:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan does not answer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.84,0:13:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He pockets the notes and walks back to the jeep, and for a second he stands at the door with his hand on it, not getting in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.20,0:13:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The jeep pulled over on an empty country road.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.33,0:14:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan stands at the edge of a field that is not part of his case — a good plot, well worked, someone's gum drying on the racks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.98,0:14:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks at it the way a man looks at a house he used to live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.41,0:14:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,A YOUNG FARMER slows his motorcycle, sees the uniform, folds his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.52,0:14:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Ram Ram, sahib.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.29,0:14:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ram Ram.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.28,0:14:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan looks at the field a moment longer, then gets back in the jeep, and it goes dark behind him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.16,0:14:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The condolence crowd has thinned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.79,0:14:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,DAULATRAM, fifty-five, the groom's uncle, prosperous and unhurried, sits where the mourners sat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.43,0:14:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Behind him stands PRATAP, forty, the groom, saying nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.13,0:14:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Bherulal receives them with both hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.52,0:14:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Very bad business, Bherulal. Who can turn aside what's fated? But we must speak of what's ahead too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.92,0:14:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course. The bond between us will hold, Daulatram-ji.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.65,0:14:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The girl is gone. And the accounts that stood — the debt, the land — those were tied to the match.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.04,0:15:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The debt... I'll repay it. Just a little time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.00,0:15:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Daulatram lets that sit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.92,0:15:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, easily:
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.24,0:15:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How old is your younger one?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.28,0:15:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Something goes across Bherulal's face.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.93,0:15:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,His elder girl is not yet in the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.00,0:15:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,...Twelve.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.77,0:15:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When she's older, we'll talk. Keep the accounts square.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.12,0:15:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Pratap looks at the house a moment — the dead girl's house — with flat eyes, and follows his uncle out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.94,0:15:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Bherulal stands where they left him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.60,0:15:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The women's side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.78,0:15:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,An older relative, the AUNT, sorts through Leela's things into a cloth bundle to be given away, the way it is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.80,0:15:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Bherulal's younger daughter, NANHI, twelve, sits against the wall watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.03,0:15:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,SUGNA is on the floor, not helping, her hands in her lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.28,0:15:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The aunt holds up a kameez, decides, folds it into the bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.96,0:15:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do keeping these? They'll serve someone in need.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.92,0:15:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sugna says nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.22,0:15:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Nanhi watches a green dupatta go into the bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.84,0:16:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's my sister's.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.07,0:16:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, child. Your sister isn't here anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.72,0:16:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Nanhi looks at her mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.43,0:16:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Sugna does not look back at her, or at the bundle, or at anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.77,0:16:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Her hands stay folded in her lap as the last of the girl goes into the cloth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.12,0:16:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Mishra is on the phone, listening far more than he speaks, his face gone careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.55,0:16:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He puts it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.81,0:16:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan is at the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.76,0:16:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan. Come in. A call just came. From above.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.38,0:16:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,From whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.96,0:16:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,They were asking why the Bherulal matter still isn't closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.24,0:16:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the report come, sahib.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.48,0:16:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Mishra comes around the desk, and what is in his voice now is almost kindness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.96,0:16:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty-five years you've served. Two years left, your pension in sight. For one dead girl you'll take on the men at the top? They'll ruin you in a single stroke. Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.07,0:16:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.13,0:16:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Then close it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.27,0:16:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the report come.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.88,0:17:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mishra looks at him a long moment, the way you look at a man walking into something, and lets him go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.00,0:17:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,A narrow lane, a wall, the back of the government school.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.59,0:17:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,RESHMA, sixteen, in school uniform, walking fast with her bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.58,0:17:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan falls in beside her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.67,0:17:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,She does not stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.40,0:17:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You were Leela's friend. Reshma.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.83,0:17:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything, sahib.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.00,0:17:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He holds out the Ratlam handbill, folded soft.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.80,0:17:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This was with her. A coaching slip, from Ratlam. I haven't come to trap her, child. I've come to learn what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.48,0:17:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Reshma slows.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.40,0:17:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,She looks back down the empty lane once.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.52,0:17:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,She wanted to study. Further. Go to Ratlam. She was saving money, in secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.81,0:17:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In secret from whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.13,0:18:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,From her family. Her marriage was fixed — to that man who was much older. Leela used to say: I won't go there. I'll run, I'll study.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.88,0:18:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The lane is quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.07,0:18:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Reshma's eyes fill, and she wipes them with the back of her wrist, angry at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.56,0:18:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sahib, don't tell anyone my name. I have to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.53,0:18:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Did anyone help her? To run?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.48,0:18:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But she has already pulled her bag up and gone, fast, the way you go when you have said one word too many.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.16,0:18:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The jeep on a dark road, the fields black on both sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.68,0:18:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Deva drives.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.65,0:18:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan beside him, the day behind his eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.32,0:18:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,She was running. From the very man she was promised to. Forty years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.59,0:18:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty. And Leela sixteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.12,0:18:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They drive a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.44,0:18:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Sahib... there's talk for my sister too. Good boy, land, a license. I'm to go meet them, day after tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.84,0:18:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Did your sister say yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.32,0:18:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Deva opens his mouth to answer, and finds he does not have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.00,0:18:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,...I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.16,0:19:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan looks out at the dark fields and does not say anything, and lets the boy sit with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.80,0:19:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Morning, the family at tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.96,0:19:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,BAPU is dressed to go — the visit to the boy's family is today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.00,0:19:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,AMMA presses a clean shirt on Deva.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.80,0:19:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunita pours, eyes down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.00,0:19:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Deva, it's getting late. Girdhari will be waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.60,0:19:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Deva does not get up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.72,0:19:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Bapu. Did we ask her? Sunita?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.48,0:19:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The room stops a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.35,0:19:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Bapu turns.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.48,0:19:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of talk is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.11,0:19:32.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We just ask. Once. You say it. Do you want to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.40,0:19:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunita's hand stays on the kettle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.56,0:19:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole house waits on her, and for a moment it is not certain what she will say.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.12,0:19:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A small house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.18,0:19:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan eats alone at the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.46,0:19:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,His wife, KANTA, clears a pot in the back, the two of them long past needing to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.00,0:19:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A knock.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.61,0:19:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,At the door, A MAN — pressed shirt, calm, the kind that is never quite introduced.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.12,0:20:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan sahib. Forgive the late hour. Two minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.76,0:20:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He steps in only as far as he needs to, and sets a thick envelope on the edge of the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.48,0:20:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bherulal matter. There's a wish from above that it close quickly. An accident, that's all. And this — for your trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.28,0:20:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan looks at the envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.21,0:20:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He has taken a hundred of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.41,0:20:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Kanta, in the back, does not turn around.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.52,0:20:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Whose wish?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.25,0:20:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a sensible man.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.28,0:20:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The envelope sits between them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.19,0:20:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be the easiest thing in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.83,0:20:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Then Ratan slides it back across the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.76,0:20:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Not this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.68,0:20:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The smile goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.32,0:20:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Think it over, sahib. This road won't be good for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.78,0:20:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gotten very late.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.16,0:20:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The man takes his envelope and goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.96,0:20:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan sits.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.82,0:20:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,After a while Kanta speaks from the back, not unkind, not hopeful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.24,0:20:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,What fight are you picking at this age?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.84,0:20:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan does not answer her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.75,0:20:57.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks at the door the man left by.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.76,0:20:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Late, the office empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.38,0:21:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ratan sits with Leela's thin file open under the lamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.19,0:21:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Her school photo is clipped to the corner — a girl grinning crooked at a camera, a board exam three weeks off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.94,0:21:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks at it for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.40,0:21:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The mourners are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.82,0:21:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The house is dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.98,0:21:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,SUGNA sits alone against the wall where the women keened all day, her daughter's folded clothes in her lap, her hands still on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.49,0:21:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The camera holds on her, on her hands on the folded clothes, and does not move either.
